{"display":"Use the notebooklm skill to perform iterative deep research on a NotebookLM\nI just prepared. Notebook URL: https://notebooklm.google.com/notebook/6066354e-2821-4fb3-8592-a6d8f238ede2\n\nWorkflow:\n\n1. Check auth status. If not authenticated, run auth_manager.py setup and\n   tell me to log in.\n\n2. Smart-add the notebook to my library:\n   - First query: \"What is the content of this notebook? What topics are\n     covered? Provide a complete overview briefly and concisely.\"\n   - Then add it with:\n     --name \"Xiaomi AX3000T Docs\"\n     --description \"<derived from the discovery query>\"\n     --topics \"xiaomi,ax3000t,router,mesh,wifi6,openwrt,home-networking\"\n   - Activate it.\n\n3. Run a structured research pass on optimal configuration for THREE\n   AX3000T units in a single home, asking ONE question per call and\n   following up only when there's a real gap. Budget: max 15 queries\n   total (rate limit is 50/day, leave headroom).\n\n   Ask in this order, treating each as independent (each call has no\n   memory of previous calls — include context in every question):\n\n   Q1. \"For three Xiaomi AX3000T routers deployed as a mesh in one home,\n   what does the documentation recommend for topology: wired Ethernet\n   backhaul vs wireless backhaul, star vs daisy-chain, and physical\n   placement of the three nodes (gateway/mid/edge)?\"\n\n   Q2. \"For a 3-node Xiaomi AX3000T mesh, what are the recommended 5 GHz\n   channel width settings (20/40/80/160 MHz), DFS channel usage, and\n   channel selection strategy?\"\n\n   Q3. \"For a 3-node Xiaomi AX3000T mesh, what are the recommended 2.4 GHz\n   configuration, transmit power levels, and band-steering / smart-\n   connect / 802.11k/v/r fast-roaming settings?\"\n\n   Q4. \"On Xiaomi AX3000T, compare stock MiWiFi firmware vs OpenWrt for a\n   3-node mesh: stability, feature parity, mesh support, and which\n   firmware version is currently recommended.\"\n\n   Q5. \"For a Xiaomi AX3000T mesh, what is the recommended security\n   configuration: WPA3 vs WPA2/WPA3 mixed, PMF, guest network\n   isolation, IoT VLAN segmentation, and firmware update policy?\"\n\n   Q6. \"For a 3-node Xiaomi AX3000T mesh, what QoS, IPv6, DNS (local\n   resolver, DoH/DoT), and hardware NAT / flow-offloading settings\n   are recommended?\"\n\n   Q7. \"What are the most commonly reported bugs and issues with the\n   Xiaomi AX3000T in mesh mode, and what are the documented\n   workarounds, reset procedures, and re-pairing steps?\"\n\n   Q8. \"Across all sources in this notebook, where do official Xiaomi\n   documentation and community sources (Reddit/Quora/forums)\n   DISAGREE about AX3000T mesh configuration, and which view has\n   stronger evidence?\"\n\n4. After each answer, when you see \"Is that ALL you need to know?\",\n   evaluate: if the answer cited specific values/settings with sources,\n   move on. If it was vague or contradictory, ask ONE focused follow-up\n   only.\n\n5. After all questions, synthesize a single markdown report with sections\n   matching Q1–Q8, with citations to which source(s) supported each\n   recommendation. Flag any UNVERIFIED claim. Save it to\n   ~/Documents/ax3000t-mesh-research.md (or print it if outside that path).\n\nConstraints:\n\n- Each question is stateless — restate context in every question.\n- Do NOT ask more than 2 follow-ups per main question.\n- Stop and tell me if you hit the rate limit.","pastedContents":{"1":{"id":1,"type":"text","contentHash":"f730e1742a1be3a5"},"2":{"id":2,"type":"text","contentHash":"599d90e161fa1112"}},"timestamp":1777657391013,"project":"/Users/juliano.barbosa/Repos/github/notebooklm_source_automation","sessionId":"7df82af7-eff7-482e-a684-2e33f86aeb01"}
